<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="93" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
This species was first described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mathiesen-Kaeaerik, A" journalOrPublisher="Meddeland Statens Skogs-Forskningsinst" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 74" refId="B31" refString="Mathiesen-Kaeaerik, A, 1953. Eine Uebersicht ueber die gewoehnlichsten mit Borkenkaefern assoziierten Blaeuepilze in Schweden und einige fuer Schweden neue Blaeuepilze. Meddeland Statens Skogs-Forskningsinst 43: 1 - 74" title="Eine Uebersicht ueber die gewoehnlichsten mit Borkenkaefern assoziierten Blaeuepilze in Schweden und einige fuer Schweden neue Blaeuepilze." volume="43" year="1953">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mathiesen-Käärik">Mathiesen-Kaeaerik</normalizedToken>
(1953)
</bibRefCitation>
from pine timber in Sweden. No specimen numbers and very little detail (e.g. no host locality or collection dates) were provided in the protologue. Furthermore, no specimen number and little detail are listed under this species name in the herbarium of the Museum of Evolution, Uppsala, which incorporated 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mathiesen-Käärik’s">Mathiesen-Kaeaerik's</normalizedToken>
collection. However, in 1954 she deposited an isolate (No. Sk 13-52) in the CBS labeled as 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. erubescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="erubescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. erubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Two dried specimens (CBS H-7193, CBS H-7194) are linked to this isolate and these are labeled as isotypes. It is reasonable to assume that this isolate represents the original material, but there is no conclusive evidence that this is true. We have thus designated the line drawings from the protologue (
<bibRefCitation author="Mathiesen-Kaeaerik, A" journalOrPublisher="Meddeland Statens Skogs-Forskningsinst" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 74" refId="B31" refString="Mathiesen-Kaeaerik, A, 1953. Eine Uebersicht ueber die gewoehnlichsten mit Borkenkaefern assoziierten Blaeuepilze in Schweden und einige fuer Schweden neue Blaeuepilze. Meddeland Statens Skogs-Forskningsinst 43: 1 - 74" title="Eine Uebersicht ueber die gewoehnlichsten mit Borkenkaefern assoziierten Blaeuepilze in Schweden und einige fuer Schweden neue Blaeuepilze." volume="43" year="1953">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mathiesen-Käärik">Mathiesen-Kaeaerik</normalizedToken>
1953
</bibRefCitation>
) as the lectotype.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="93">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2001.12061284" author="Harrington, TC" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" pagination="111 - 136" refId="B13" refString="Harrington, TC, McNew, D, Steimel, J, Hofstra, D, Farrel, R, 2001. Phylogeny and taxonomy of the Ophiostomapiceae complex and the Dutch elm disease fungi. Mycologia 93: 111 - 136" title="Phylogeny and taxonomy of the Ophiostomapiceae complex and the Dutch elm disease fungi." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00275514.2001.12061284" volume="93" year="2001">Harrington et al., (2001)</bibRefCitation>
suggested that 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Microascaceae" genus="Graphium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Graphium erubescens" order="Microascales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="erubescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Graphium erubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName class="Sordariomycetes" family="Ophiostomataceae" genus="Phialographium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Phialographium erubescens" order="Ophiostomatales" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="erubescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">Phialographium erubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) represented the asexual state of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. cucullatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="cucullatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. cucullatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(as 
<taxonomicName genus="O." lsidName="O. cucullatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="cucullatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">O. cucullatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) based on ITS sequences. However, based on sequences produced in the present study, the ex-type culture of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. erubescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="erubescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. erubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from that of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. cucullatum" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="cucullatum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. cucullatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 1bp in ITS2-LSU, 17 bp in ACT, 17 bp in BT, 30 bp in CAL, and 48 bp in TEF-1α. We have thus treated these species as distinct and have provided a new combination for 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. erubescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="93" rank="species" species="erubescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="93">L. erubescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
